No fewer than five ministers of the Redeemed Christian Church of God (RCCG) have been abducted on their way to attend the church’s Ministers’ Conference in Lagos. The General Overseer of the RCCG, Pastor Enoch Adeboye confirmed the abduction on Friday while giving a talk at the Redeemed Camp along the Lagos-Ibadan Expressway. The General Overseer said this is the first time such incident of that magnitude was happening. He urged members to pray for the release of the abducted pastors.  